# Frontend Assessment — AI Learning Labs

A responsive frontend built with plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. No frameworks, no build tools.

## What's Inside

### Exercise 1 — Landing Page

A hero slider at the top with product cards below.

The slider auto-plays, loops infinitely, and supports swipe on touch screens. There are prev/next arrows and clickable dots to jump between slides.

The product grid below shows 4 cards per row on desktop, 3 on tablet, and 2 on mobile. Each card has an image area, brand name, product title, and pricing.

### Exercise 2 — Tabs and Accordion

On desktop this works as a tab bar — click a tab to switch panels. Arrow keys also work to move between tabs.

On mobile the same content turns into an accordion. Each section can be expanded or collapsed. The first one is open by default.

## How to Run

No setup needed. Just open the file:

```
open index.html
```

Or use a simple local server if you prefer:

```
npx serve .
```

Then go to `http://localhost:3000` in your browser.

## File Structure

```
/
├── index.html
├── css/
│   └── style.css
├── js/
│   └── main.js
└── README.md
```

## Responsive Breakpoints

| Screen Size | Product Grid | Navigation |
|---|---|---|
| Above 1024px | 4 columns | Tabs |
| 769px to 1024px | 3 columns | Tabs |
| 768px and below | 2 columns | Accordion |
| 480px and below | 2 columns, compact spacing | Accordion |

## Tech Used

- HTML5
- CSS3 with grid, flexbox, and media queries
- JavaScript ES6, no libraries
